caption: Wow. This place was a blast. Super cool outside seating and lounge area. The food and the beer were both top notch. We will be visiting again even if it is an hour and a half drive from home.
Great place, good ambience and amazing beer! I've been here couple of times and the servers are really good and helpful and can recommend good beer to you depending on your preferences!

Absolutely loved this place!! They have a great selection of beers and the food is really delicious as well. The outdoor seating was very well done, spaced out and heated. We had several beers here and I remember every one enjoying their beers. I had the Chapless Horseman and the Noccila both of them were AMAZING! This place is walking distance from my place, definitely going here over and over again.
Great scene great beers! Outdoors Covid safe and friendly.  Good heating for outside dining!
They have a great social distancing,  and all the staff are incredibly friendly and accommodating. Would definitely recommend as part of a silver spring brewery crawl.
Great place for a couple of beers, even in the winter! We'll spaced for Covid, and great service
Great outdoor seating (even in winter). Loved our personal fire pit!

I was actually just walking by it, for the first time, but it looks really nice inside and place I'd want to go to sample beer and hangout out with some friends if I was still drinking . Maybe I'll swing by one day if any of my beer drinking friends are in town . I hope so ! I really liked walking down the side of the building, which I hadn't known existed . It brings you too a pleasant alleyway that has an ice cream shop and outdoor seating for the brewery !
Great food and drinks, put a lot of effort into ensuring guests and staff we're safe. Wouldn't hesitate to come back or order pickup/delivery.

Great beer, nice environment. Very good about COVID regulations, which is actually the main reason why I wanted to be sure I posted a review. While I was there, I accidentally forgot to put my mask back on when I was on my way to the bathroom, and I was very happy to be reminded by a staff member before I got too far. Thank you for keeping your patrons and the community safe!!

Even during this pandemic, every worker did there part. Thoroughly enjoyed visiting and the beer selection was amazing. Sat outside with no worries about being super close to others.  Multiple beers on draft outside and ordering was easy!
Really good beer, good fries too

Been a loyal- weekly customer for over a year. Today was last straw, as we've had multiple bad customer service situations at Denizen over the past 2 years. Today we were  asked to move from a table because a party was waiting, at the moment  for it.  We asked the host if the party already arrived and we were told yes they were in line checking in so we had to move. We moved, sat another table for an hour and the table we gave up remained empty until we left. This is not the first customer disservice I've experienced here, but this was the last straw. I was with my husband whose been a weekly customer for over 2 years. We won't be back. Management and supervisors know us by face yet they still continue to treat us second class. Goodbye denizen.   10/5 reply : As I said this is NOT the first customer disservice we've experienced here. Also I'm writing this at my husband's request because he was not ok at all. An apology was owed. He's spent thousands of dollars at Denizen since you've been open. He's disgusted at how's he's been treated. He's also a manager in customer service so we comprehend and understand very well the correct way to treat a customer.
Great outdoor place with really good beer and food! Doing a great job with social distancing. Little fire pits and pumpkins add to the ambiance. Make a reservation or you will be disappointed...
Missed this place. First meal out. Pretzel and Brussels sprouts apps tasty. Draft mead and some beers. Brisket and earth burger foods. Not enough tummy space for churros
The only bar experience I've had since COVID.  They work to make it super COVID safe and comfortable.  And, of course, they have great beer.
Socially distanced tables, an easy reservation system, great customer service, friendly staff, and good food and drink. Also dogs. What more could you want?
Great beer and food. Thanks!

Denizens is the only place we’ve gone out to since the pandemic began and I can’t recommend it more. We are a super cautious household and I felt so safe the whole time. The tables are actually far enough apart to feel social distanced, the wait staff was double masked, you could decided if you wanted your table bussed or not, and they cleaned pens after they were used. Definitely get a reservation if you want to go on the weekend, a lot of disappointed people were turned away. Beer and snacks are excellent as always, but it was so great to get out and still feel safe.
Well thought out outdoor dining experience!
Great food and beer, plus a good outside area so you don't catch the Rona.
BEST BEER!!!!

Great place, worth a visit. I really loved the chicken wings, perfectly good a little extra salt but goes well with the ranch dip. The fish tacos were pretty decent, although the fish was bland but went well overalll. Perfecly well cooked churros, the chocolate dip was little runny but tasted awsome. The service was a little delayed due to pandemic, wasnt very satisfied but overall good experience. Loved the unexpected fireworks.
We love the food & staff!! The 2 pups love the french Fries even more ;)
Food is amazing and the beer, even better. You have to walk up to the bar to order your beer and food since waiters don’t come to your table, which is totally fine.
We had a great time at Denizens. The food is good, the beer is great, and we felt very safe sitting outside.
Another good time at Denizens in Silver Spring. Fish tacos were very good and the beer was great, as usual.
Delicious food and comfortable patio.

Relaxing evening with family at Denizens in Silver Spring. Easy reservation system, immediate seating, comfortable and safe dining under a large tent. Besides their usual excellent beer they now have several delicious cocktails. Definitely recommend you visit soon.

Fantastic beers.  Very good delivery service that will deliver beer to your house on a no-contact basis.  The first time they deliver to you, just tape your driver's license to the window so that they can "card" you.  Favorites are their Born Bohemian pilsner,  Lowest Lord ESB, Georgia Ave Sour.  Limited release Papagayo (a brett saison) is great too.  PGC Premium Lager is not to my taste.
Sours are not sour enough or fruit forward enough. Food is decent. Brussel sprouts are very good but could use a bit more blue cheese.

Had a very nice experience here last night. Appreciated the tents which kept everything cool.  Tables were nicely distanced from each other, particularly important since there were people at every table, felt safe overall. Food was really good -  the house made veggie/earth burger was AMAZING, probably the best veggie burger I have ever had... and I have had a lot. Mac n cheese, Brussels, fries also were really good. Yummy all around.🌟

Amazing beer, great food, and wonderful staff! Denizens always has a great selection on draft and for purchase in cans or growlers. Love that they have added terrific hard selzers to the mix. They are also handling the COVID restrictions very well. The outdoor area is spacious and under a big tent so you can visit rain or shine. Cannot wait to go back.
I just came here a little over a week ago and their social distancing measures are great and staff was very helpful and friendly.
great spot - great tent - great beers and food

I've been to Denizen's several times now since safety measures around social distancing have been put into place and it's always a positive experience. I appreciate how seriously they've taken the guidelines to keep their staff and customers as safe as possible during these times, while still being a great experience for the customer.
The best. Have shifted beautifully to COVID dining. Love the tent -- hope they keep it!
Denizens is doing SUCH a great job of social distancing and precautions. Plus they’re rolling out new beers all the time. I tried the Papagayo today and it was perfect for a hot summer afternoon.

This is an amazing place! It has one of the best house-made veggie burgers in the area! Super tasty and it does not desintegrate as most others do! The brussel sprouts add a great crunch! It comes with fries which are amazing!! Super generous portion too! The crabcake is excellent! And the beer and cocktails are delicious! Largest covered outdoor seating in the area. So rain or shine you are good! Casual picnic benches and comfy loungy chairs. Excellent Covid19 measures. We felt taken care off by the attentive staff but also safe with proper social distancing. Definitely a must-go!!!

They did a great job on Covid-prep and maintaining space, and were friendly and helpful. Some of the seasonal beers were very good, and the bar food we noshed on was tasty and exactly what we wanted. (Note: This was exactly the second time we’d attempted an outdoor, socially distanced outing to a restaurant/bar, and they really went above and beyond to make sure we understood what they were doing to prevent spread and also what their expectations of customers were - a comprehensive strategy... I’m still a bit nervous going anywhere, but can recommend denizens as a good option for the risk adverse who - for whatever reason - need to get out!)
Delicious beer and veggie burger on a great shady patio. The staff were all super nice. It wasn't crowded and we felt very safe.

Terrific afternoon in Denizens beer garden! Great beer and food (yum Brussels sprouts!). Relaxed Atmosphere but very careful attention to health & safety of customers and staff. Will definitely be back soon!
Outdoor seating was easy to reserve, the beer was great and my steak sandwich was fantastic too!
They had a good set-up and the beers and churros were delicious!
We have a great (and safe) experience here every time we go.
Doing a great job with spacing and keeping it safe!
0 hospitality, it is opened to make a money not to serve a customers.
Denizens is doing it right! Great food, beer, and cocktails! They are on point with their Covid organization and safety protocol. Well done! Great shirts and hats too. Very reasonably priced!

Who charges a $50 cancellation fee for a bar reservation. Seriously what are you thinking? Doctors offices don’t even charge this much for a cancelled appointment. I just want to point out how incredibly stingy this makes your business look. Whoever made this decision needs to rethink why they joined the restaurant business. I lost a lot of respect for your business after seeing this.
Great outside seating area, food is great and distancing is well encouraged

7/23/2020: Excellent socially distanced outdoor seating. Large canopy provides shade and protection from rain without impeding air circulation. Great job rethinking the outdoor beer garden for the current situation.
Very impressed with the way Denizen's is handling covid safety safeguards.  We had a lovely dinner and drinks in a pleasant and safe environment.

I went to Denizens to celebrate my birthday this last weekend. My fiancé got reserved seating (2 hour limit), which I would recommend because it's a little limited due to Covid. This worked out well and we got a great seat on the couches, and the covered patio was very nice with how hot it is outside.  Beers were good and we got a couple to-go. I really enjoyed the Georgia Ave. Sour. The Brussels sprouts and the pretzel were excellent. Some others in our party got burgers and they were super generous portions with tons of fries.  The only negative I will mention is the outside food policy. I had brought some homemade cupcakes for my birthday. When we walked in, we were told that there can't be outside food or drink. That's okay (although I will say a little atypical for a brewery which typically have more relaxed policies for things like birthday cake), but then we're told that we can pay a $25 cake fee to eat our cupcakes there. I would understand if we were having a big party and expected Denizens to help us cut and serve a cake, but I had just brought 6 cupcakes on a plate to share with our family.  We ended up eating the cupcakes outside, right after we left, which felt a little silly, but I wasn't about to pay $25 just to eat 6 cupcakes on the patio. I hope that Denizens rethinks this policy, or maybe offers a little flexibility for smaller groups (Maybe just a $10 fee? $25 was more than the cost of the cupcakes). I totally get that this is their policy and it's their prerogative, but the experience left a sour taste in my mouth and I definitely enjoyed my experience there less than I would have otherwise.  I will also add that I skimmed Denizens website and don't see any mention of this policy. Maybe I should have expected it, given that they serve food there, but I was honestly surprised by this.
Great set up, with covered outdoor seating. Well spaced from other guests for social distancing. Great food, beer and cocktails.

I had only been to Denizens once before in the winter and I was apprehensive about meeting there on a 90+ degree day today. However, the outdoor beer garden set up was fantastic for both the heat and COVID-19. The beers are great and while I didn’t have any food, the food at nearby tables looked amazing.  As far as I know, dogs are allowed in the beer garden and I can’t wait to bring my pup by for a pint. For non-beer drinkers, they have hard seltzer, wine, mead, and cocktails (made for 2-3 servings) also for sale.  Staff were very friendly and accommodating too. There is definitely a neighborhood feel to this brewery.

They’re doing everything right at Denizens. Reservations only, all outside under a big tent, masks required, way spaced out tables, self-serve food and beverages, single occupancy bathrooms. It was my first night out since March and it was great to be amongst the peeps. Good beer, good food. My only concern was that drunk people (including myself) don’t remember social distancing so be vigilant!

Denizens has always been a great place to hang out, drink a beer, and connect with friends. When they announced their reopening with outdoor seating and new safety measures, I knew I could trust them and their patrons to provide and respect social distancing guidelines. Denizens had a great system in place and it worked well. Servers worked together to seat and serve patrons quickly while keeping everything sanitized. Tables were spaced far apart to keep groups a proper distance apart. And of course the beer is always top notch! Definitely recommend booking a table with them. They're taking the pandemic seriously and are observing all of the strict guidelines that keep everyone safe and healthy!

The new tent in the Biergarten is amazing! We visited on a day it poured rain, and we stayed as dry as we could possibly have been! The staff worked tirelessly to squeegee the extra water from the floor and mopping tables off. The food and beer were delicious as always. Love, love love the brussels sprouts!!!

Want to start going out? This is THE place to choose. Great social distancing. Reservations that guaranty you a table when you arrive. Friendly service. And, of course, great brews. What are you waiting for?

One of my favorite breweries. There's always something new on the list, the flagships are great, and the staff are top notch. Friendly, strong recommendations from snacks to beer, and all over things. The tent on the patio is a welcome reprieve from the sun, and bar service is seamless. Absolutely worth a visit! Try the maibock!

Kicked off our July 4th celebration by returning to the beer garden for the first time since reopening! Impressed by the safety protocols and attention to detail. Cool and shady under the tent! Of course, the beer was just as delicious as ever! Thanks to the Denizens team for your hard work and care for the community!

Denizens is an awesome local brewery in downtown Silver Spring that is providing a good socially distant experience for its visitors. Good outdoor table spacing, single occupancy bathrooms, and seems to be doing quite a bit to keep staff safe, too! The Georgia Ave peach sour and the Moco seltzer are two new summer musts!!

I visited a lot before covid-19 and it was one of the first places I return to after things started to open up. The staff was amazing and went over all the new guidelines at each vist. I feel safe going here during this situation and will continue to return.

After four months in quarantine, my husband and I were looking forward to a night out but also nervous about the idea. Denizen’s went above and beyond in their precautions and we immediately felt at ease. There was a separate entrance and exit, tables were appropriately distanced, everything was ordered from the bar while wearing a mask, and reservations were limited to two hours which was the perfect  amount of time. The food and drinks were great and it was so nice to feel somewhat normal for two hours. Highly recommend!
Had a great evening at Denizens last night. Everything ran smooth as the new oyster stout.

It was really nice to be back at Denizens for thirst-quenching beer, yummy food, and friendly service.  They are doing a good job of keeping outdoor seating and service save.  The line for food/drink was slow, but hopefully if more of us come to visit the management can add an extra cashier! Remember to make a reservation--
Love Denizens and their beer selections. Also the earth burger is my favorite veggie burger in DC! They took great care in making sure all patrons were socially distanced in the outdoor beer garden.
Great local spot for a drink! Highly recommend trying their new cherry sour Sligo Kriek - delicious!
Great place to hang and drink

After this pandemic it has been difficult to find places to go to socialize safely.  Denizen is so awesome! Outdoor picnic seating with individual umbrellas and soft AstroTurf to walk on.  They have a real Beer brewery feel with the addition of a full menu and really good food, you can’t beat Denizen.  Great!!

Great service. Had rhe crab cake it was ok, was expecting more of chunky crabs thank shredded crabs. With the CoVid19 they have a 2 hour limit to dine in. Reservations are not required but I will recommend it due to restricted seating.

We were so happy to return to Denizen's beer garden. We love their beer and food. Our only complaint is that there were people in line and milling around who were not wearing masks and no one was asking them to put them on. We would feel safer if policies were enforced. This was also the case when we came a few days earlier but left after the rain had apparently cancelled our reservation.

We visited Denizens in June after their outdoor seating opened up again. It was so nice to be able to get out of the house and enjoy the evening. It was easy to make a reservation online, and we were seated right away when we arrived. The outdoor space is comfortable and roomy, and the team is taking infection prevention measures seriously. The beer was very good, as always and we enjoyed our burgers. We will be back this summer for sure!

Had a great father's day experience here with wife and the kids.  Outside patio was a great environment, food is awesome as usual and a great beer selection.  Glad they are open, and they are taking the rules seriously.

Love this beer garden!  Met up with my son for Father's Day, and really appreciated the way Denizens handled social distancing and safety.  The reservations system was easy, and the check-in/seating was smooth.  The little sign for "Service" / "No Service" was clever -- and the staff was there basically immediately when requested.  Of course, the whole point is the beer, which was great.  I am a fan of the Dublate (double IPA)!  Had the pulled pork sandwich with fries, and highly recommend it.  Denizens staff was great, highly recommend making your reservation and bringing your dog.
such a beautiful place to be.
Friendly staff, great beer, good food!
Denizen's is as much an "experience" and community as it is a brewpub.  Really wonderful staff.

A nice first meal out after months of quarantine! Plenty of room between tables. The staff had a clear and well-planned system in place to ensure social distancing and sanitation. Food and beers were tasty as always.

I was so happy to back at Denizens - a place that makes me always feel right at home. The beer, as always, was delicious and the vibe was super relaxed (but also safe). This place has become a local institution and I'm so grateful to have it!
Attentive and friendly staff. Beers are great and awesome outdoor space. Seemed pretty accessible and while there weren't any all-gender restrooms it was LGBT friendly.
Get drunk while having the best food!

This spot is handling social distancing very well - reserve ahead to be seated quickly. Food is so tasty, especially the Garden burger which is crispy and flavorful, nothing like the soggy veggie burger you have in your mind. Fries are crisp, beer is cold, and the patio is a great place to unwind.
Doing a fantastic job with safe reopening!!
Thank you for my first night out in the COVID-19 world.  Delicious food and drink, fun outdoor tables, and a ton of distancing/safety measures that made us all comfortable.  Thank you!
Overhyped and not good beer. Seriously disappointing.
The food, beer and service were all great.

Honestly, one of the worst experiences I've ever had at a bar/brewery. I came here last year with some of my coworkers and the server was completely oblivious to what we ordered (2 different drink's were brought out by mistake). Food was cold after we ordered it, I asked for his recommendation and he didn't really know. He didn't engage with our party at all (It was a party of 10-12 people). Overall I had a decent time with my coworkers but I definitively won't be returning or wasting my time here again. I understand if you are new to the role/position but than you should speak up and explain that, otherwise people are going to make assumptions and question his competency. He didn't apologize or try to be emphatic toward the situation. Some people just aren't people "persons" and don't need to be in that kind of job.  The only reason I wrote this review is a friend was asking me recommendations for bar's in the area and I remembered what a horrible time we had here from before.

It's a solid spot with great food and brews.. I'm a stout fan myself...during the warmer months it's a nice outdoor area with TVs. Very open space for socializing and a good time with friends.. food is very good as well.. the parmesan truffle fries along with the dry rub wings..dope combination...I don't know why I won't give it 5 🌟.... I'll think about it.. right now just 4
A+ patio, especially on the rare warm winter days...

My housemates and I enjoy going to Denizen’s during the summer for a beer in the garden. If it’s too hot, try sitting inside or downstairs to beat the heat. They have plenty of events ranging from live DJ’s to Trivia during the summer that bring a wide range of folks to the brewery which kicks the chill mode up to a lively crowd - so depending on what kind of mood you’re in, you’ll likely find it here. I don’t eat there very often so I can’t attest to the food, but the staff are friendly and the service pretty quick.

We’re on vacation and decided to find a local brewery. Denizens’ selection of beers are delicious. Their various styles of beers have a lot of character: from stouts, IPAs to sours. I had the falafel sliders and they are very tasty and moist. The blonde is a shareable size and taste pretty decent as well. The decor is cozy yet spacious without that sterile and cold feel that some newer breweries have. We’re here in Silver Spring for a few days and have decided that we’ll be returning in the next couple of days. The service is excellent and everyone takes care of you. I highly recommend stopping by Denizens if you find yourself in the area.
Good spot for a quick beer and some late night eats!

I was visiting the area for just one night to catch up with a friend and chose Denizens with nothing to go on but the website. We ended up having a brilliant night. The beer selection was excellent and the food was tasty. Our waitress was really nice and although she was rushed off her feet, service was personal and welcoming. Not 5 stars because of the attitude and rudeness of the barman. I planned to sit at the bar initially but he was abrupt, unsmiling and unwelcoming. I chose a table instead and planned to find somewhere else to take my friend; I didn't want to give my business to somewhere with such rude staff. The waitress saved the day - she was friendly and welcoming so we decided to stay. The barman stayed stand-offish all night; he brought drinks across to us when the waitress was busy and slammed them on the table without speaking. The space itself is great - warm, cosy and with a fab atmosphere, I hope to be back someday 🍻
Always a good time. Beers are solid and the food is great. Very friendly and accommodating staff. Talked to the bartender a bit about footfall while enjoying my breakfast sandwich.
Great vibes! Way to support local artists!
Beer good. I was just told by staff that a woman he was staring at is why I was completely ignored at the bar
Great food for a brewery! Also beers are good but the dressing for the Brussel sprouts was amazing. The beer cheese lacked some salt, but staff is very friendly and had a great experience.
the beers were great, just not the price though
The beer is great and the food is surprisingly good. Great atmosphere too. My favorite of the breweries in the area.

The beer, atmosphere, seating and location were all good.  Food was way over priced for the quantity and quality that I received.  In hind sight, I should have been alerted when the waiter didn't ask me how I wanted my burger cooked.  I'll take the hit for walking into that one.  Next time I'll show up thirsty but not hungry.  Overall nice place that I will definitely hit up again for a cold beer.

A Million Times YES.  I've been coming here since they opened and if anything, their already outstanding beers have gotten better- and I know beer, I make it.  Their food menu/setup/chef has changed so many times, I'm just going to say that it's always been good food and moderately priced and leave it at that.  The basement space and outdoor space provide a great atmosphere, the upstairs has couches and chairs for lounging when it's not too crowded.  Recommendations:  If you know your beers (if not, chat with your waiter) select two or maybe three and ask for a small sample and choose your favorite.  Sours are not for everybody but if you appreciate them like I do, theirs are excellent, as are the higher ABV Trippels when they're available.  Definitely stop in and ENJOY!
Food was alright but serve staff was EXCELLENT

The best part of this place is the patio. The patio is wonderful. The beers are so so. The prices are outrageous. This used to be a favorite of mine in Silver Spring. Silver Spring has gotten better. This place hasn't.

Very simple concept: good beer (coming from a german so I know what I'm talking about) and tasty food. Relatively expensive for german standards but most definetly worth it. Will come again should I visit this area again!

My daughter says they serve the best pulled pork sandwich she’s ever had. She’s an 11 year old aspiring chef, so take from that what you will :) In truth though, it is a really good sandwich. The bottom line is, this is a really good brewery with very good food and a great beer selection. Awesome outdoor social and live band seating area and all in downtown Silver Spring. I highly suggest Denizens, especially on a nice evening; if you want a good beer and burger and maybe the opportunity to hang outside with friends or meet some new people.
The patio is the right place to hang out with friends. The food is just okay though.

My boyfriend and I came here in on a Friday afternoon and while the food was good and the beer okay, I don’t think we will be back. It was $50 for 1 cheeseburger, a pint, and a 4 beer flight. The beer was okay, they all tasted pretty similar and were not worth $4 each. They had a decent selection of style of beer which was appreciated but no sour in the summer....come on.  The cheeseburger was $17. That’s insane for a hockey puck sized cheeseburger with onion jam and one piece of bacon. It was tasty but I would go literally anywhere else for a cheeseburger and pay less for 2x the food. There are so many more breweries in the area with better food/beer and better prices.

It’s 2019. Serve a vegan option.  — Thanks for the response. The server & manager both said the veggie burger had egg in it. The only items I could eat were fries & a modified salad (which came after my group was finished eating because, according to the manager, the kitchen had a hard time modifying it).
I been here once and the food is really good, they have good food nice restaurant but the prices are too elevated.
The beer is good, but I did not like the veggie burger. I'm still searching for a good vb. The fries were a little soggy. Overall a good experience, given the beer was good as was the service.

Food was way below my expectations.  The octopus will be overcooked, and doesn't go with the soggy potato.  Beer was solid though.  I would go back for drinks but definitely not the food.  Service was certainly fine.
Miss the mac and cheese from the winter!

(Translated by Google) They produce local beer and can also enjoy local beers. The staff is also very friendly. Potato fries come out in great quantities. But it is delicious. I think it is good to stop by the time not too late and drink one or two cups.  (Original) 地ビールを生産していて、かつローカルビールも気軽に楽しめる。 スタッフもとてもフレンドリー。 ポテトフライはすごい量が出てくる。でも、美味しい。あまり遅くならない時間に立ち寄って1、2杯飲むスタイルが良さそう。
The beer is decent, but the space is gross and the service is terrible. Better off just buying the beer at a market and skipping the brewery visit.
Poor, waited for service to get a beer and food. No one showed up- I left and went to Silver Branch Brewing...and got a great beer and hot pretzels.
Awesome patio and great beers and food.

Denizens has a classic beer garden vibe (outdoor picnic tables) and an upscale pub menu, complete with Brussels sprouts and veggie burgers and octopus. Fun trivia on Tuesday nights, a happy hour till 6. Great seasonal beers, with solid options from IPAs to sours. Really good spot worth visiting if you're in Silver Spring!
Great place to relax and bring pups in the nice weather!
great date spot, nice for trivia in the winters, and hanging out on the beer patio during the summer.

Local microbrewery that has some nice beers. The selection is not much but what they have is very good. Their bar food selection is also tasty. For non fancy people that like a good atmosphere and great beer this is one of the best places to hangout.
Check out the paintings downstairs. Also, parm fries over everything. Thank you
Love the food, beer and nice big outdoor area where I can hang out with my pup!

I have been going to Denizens Brewing Co. since the day it opened. This will be my first review as I feel that the best way to rate a place is with foot traffic, (meaning never return or return often). I go to Denizens weekly and more often when possible. I’ll drag as many of my friends, coworkers, and family members as I can, each trip. Great Beer! Great Location! and Food that I'll take to Mom. The group of people both owners and staff have done the best of jobs in creating a welcome atmosphere for true beer lovers, and they deserve your support! Cheers to Denizens!

Denizens has a great atmosphere. Their seasonal beers are usually pretty good and the fries are the best. They have a good selection of food items that rotate seasonally and pair well with their selection of beers. They also host many community events that help engage the thriving social life Silver Spring has to offer.
Really good beer, especially the barrel-aged ones. Food is also good and reasonably priced. It was raining when we were there, but the outdoor beer garden looks amazing.
Good food, fun events, great place to hang with friends!
Nice place to have fun with friends and food and drinks were nice. Overall a nice experience of outing with friends.
Beer and food was good, but not the best I've had in the DMV. One of the better breweries, but not in my top 5.

A top craft brewery in the DMV with an amazing patio and indoor seating. The beers are very good with seasonal variety. I love Big Red Norm, Black Panther dark Lager and the Bohemian Pilsner and the Third Party Belgian style tripel. But I also love the special events they have which are well organized and offer unique selections. Warm Friday or Saturday nights on the patio are an amazing experience. Food is not bad, but not great either. Stop by, you won't be disappointed.
Brilliant barrel aged sour!  All the right kind of fun!
By far one the greatest additions to the Downtown Silver Spring area.  The outdoor experience is one of a kind and the beer is always good.  Great for large groups.

This is a great place to meet with friends, I came here once and decided to bring more friends on a second visit. The beer is great. Maybe I didn't go full five star because the food selection was short although very tasty.

Excellent beer, especially the wee heavy scotch ale.  However, I think that they really little too much on the sour stuff/Saison.  The food is very good and the service is excellent.  No corporate feel; Denizen's is a true local treasure.
SICK, NASTY, AWESOME HAPPY HOUR AND ALL AROUND BAR/STAFF! DEF WILL BE BACK!

Good brewery with 5-7 beers on tap. Couple notes. The parking is a short walk to a garage. Happy hour is all day Monday and 4 to 6 during the week. Weekends are pretty busy, especially after 6PM. Couldnt tell much about food since prefer to order chicken wings or tenders, and they are OK for a brew place. Price wise, wings plus 3 beers with tip will set you for about 45-50.
Good place with great outdoor seating. Parking can be an issue and you may have to walk a block or two but it's worth your effort.

Happy Hour was delicious! My veggie burger  was delicious (the parmesan fries come in plenty) & my boyfriend devoured the "Smash" burger. Will be taking my family there when they come to visit. It was a plus to know a 2nd location is opening in College Park this year!

Nice experience! Great setup and enjoyed the seasonal IPA. Good place to meet up with friends and the kids as it was not too quiet and they could run around (at least on a mild winter weeknight). Parking was a bit of a search and could have offered a bit more on the menu, but this place was a good find. And the food offered was good.

Chill atmosphere, good beer, impressed with some of the beers and I am not a big beer person. Good service, friendly staff, and was not too crowded for a friday night, maybe because its a holiday season, and was rainy weather.

Do not pass up Denizens if you have the chance to go! Their food was superb. Everything my family ordered was flavorful, and arrived both quickly and hot. The beer at Denizens is some of the best I've ever had. I would highly recommend starting with a flight to try as many of their beers as possible. Top choices among my family were the Ill Cru barrel-aged sour quadrupel, the Call Waiting barrel-aged wee-heavy, and the Dubplate double IPA, all of which are brewed in-house.
Great bar for after a day of work

Great beer, wonderful atmosphere. Definitely will come again.  Hosted my wedding reception here - food was off the charts great, beer was fantastic, and the space encouraged our families and guests to mingle and get to know each other.  Highly recommend their quinoa burger.

Nice beer house atmosphere.   Tried two different beers.  Both good.  Cheesy fries good.  Pretzels with mustard another good choice.   The hummus was disappointing, actually not the hummus. but the limp celery provided for dipping.  Parking nearby but plan ahead.  Solid B+.  Well worth the visit. Will be going back in the spring to experience the outside beer garden.
Good beer w simple menu with food for every one. Worth the trip. The beers were of  broad styles - IPA, English-style bitter, stout, sour, and American wheat. All true to style.
Amazing beers and fantastic food. Cozy & friendly place.

Beer is great, I had the Belgium triple.  I don’t recommend the food, it’s ok- feels like an afterthought. The burger has a sweet flavored sauce in it that ruined it for me. The fries were cold.  The bratwurst was pretty good and side salad average.
Great beer. Friendly staff. Downstairs bar was rad. Definitely coming back.
Great place to grab a few cold ones.

Come thirsty not hungry and you wont be disappointed ✌🏼✌🏼

I've been wanting to try Denizens for a long time. The beer selection is terrific and even challenging. I tried a sour that was amazing if also hard to classify as a beer. My wife had a rye IPA that was unusual and tasty. The food options tilt a bit toward too heavy on cheese and frying but it is classic "bar food" after all. Next time I go back I will have a burger. The veggie bibimbub bowl also is worth a future try.
There's a beer for everyone here and I could eat a whole meal that consisted of nothing but the Brussels Sprouts. Vegan options available.

I have been twice in the past month; my first month in Silver Spring, and Maryland for that matter. Denizens reminds me of my former watering holes (craft breweries) in my beloved North Carolina. In a ridiculously restrictive alcohol state they do the damn thing very well (I miss buying local beer at the grocery store). I expect to be a loyal Denizen's patron for as long as I am in the DCA. If you're an IPA guy or gal or whatev, try the Southside.
The Southside Rye IPA is excellent.
Our favorite beer place in Silver Spring, MD. This place has become an institution. Love their beer, their vibe, and their activism... We especially love how friendly they are to our fur baby.

My fiancé and I have visited this brewery a handful of times and we have never been disappointed. The beers, environment, and food are always wonderful! Their patio is great when it is warm outside, and their music playlist is also a plus. The brussel sprouts and the pretzel bites with cheese are good small plates! We ordered the parmesian fries when we were there last and you certainly get your money’s worth; however, the fries themselves were a bit undercooked and soggy, but they had good flavor!

This was only my second time at a Biergarten, and I loved it here. I originally had the Third Party, but it was too hoppy for me, which apparently means it taste too much like beer. Grab a flight and stay a while. Denizens offers a range of seating options from cozy downstairs digs to outdoor patio seating. Having only visited in Winter, we've been inside upstairs and down, but we're excited to visit the patio soon!

This place is a wonderful vibe. It's lively and fun. The food is pretty good too. Not a lot of vegetarian options, mostly just things you could snack on, except the quinoa burger, which is quiet good. The beer selection is excellent, this place is definitely worth a visit.

However, that partnership ended, and as such, it has been less than fantastic. Dogs are welcome but if you are afraid of dogs, you may want to consider other options as dogs are popular here, especially on a nice afternoon.

They also have wine and cider for those who don't like beer. There is a public parking lot a block from the restaurant, bring your change for the meters. You're getting 3 different experiences in one place, and all of them are good. Upstairs there is the outdoor beer garden with picnic tables and a lively crowd. If the weather is not agreeing, you can move indoors to either the small upstairs dining room or the downstairs bar and tables which are generally a bit more sedate. Finally, you can try the outdoor patio downstairs which is quiet and intimate.  The whole reason you came here of course was the beer, and Denizen's own brews go across the spectrum of styles so you're likely to find something you like. As far as food goes, I generally stay with the salads when I visit and they've never disappointed.
If you like Sour beers, at all, try the Ill Cru. It's game-changingly good. Big endorsement for their trippel and Southside Rye IPA too!
It's a good place
Loved the outdoor seating, the wings were great and of course the beer was awesome. Love that dogs are welcome. So happy you are in silver spring!
What an amazing spot. Fantastic beers, great atmosphere, wonderful staff. A must stop for any travelers seeking to explore the greater metropolitan beer scene.
Phenomenal. Great beers, great staff. Going back tomorrow to try the food.

It is a brewery, it's not 5-star dining or polished to perfection, it is a beer garden and indoor tap room. There is a great outdoor area that has over a dozen communal tables.  Go and order a beer and sit at a table with someone new. There is always a good rotating beer selection and the food is pretty decent bar food. Also, there is a huge parking lot a block to the west (Kennet Street Garage) that is free on weekends, don't bother circling for street parking. Make sure to buy your DD a lot of food.  Lots of families and kids running around so not the place to get totally wasted, though occasionally people do.  Live music selection usually starts around dark on the weekends.

Just earlier today I came here for the first time with two others. I really like the feel of the place. I love the patio, it reminds me of mcminamins(if you've ever been to Oregon). The space inside is not crowded with tables. I didn't get a chance to go downstairs, perhaps next time. My server was great and had intimate knowledge of the beer.  On reviewing the reviews, I really like that Emily(the co-owner) responds to every single one (even if they are not well done or rude).  However, I cannot give the remaining two stars for two reasons:  1. We ordered the pretzels first and they did not arrive until we had finished our meal and were ready to leave. We did really like the stone ground mustard. Is there wasabi in it?  2. This is the real problem. Each of us ordered the kitchen burger the same way, with bacon and cooked medium. We even said that it was OK if it still mooed at us. When they arrived, each of them were cooked  well done. Pretty much makes them dry. Which is incredibly unfortunate because the goat cheese and tomato jam are excellent toppings and it only failed because of the lack of moisture. The two smaller patties I think are a good idea because the toppings are less likely to slop off the backside when biting.  In the end, we did ask for a discount on the burgers because they were not cooked per the order. We did receive that discount and it was exactly what we had in mind. I do find it concerning that we had to ask for this to be rectified, rather than the shift manager coming to our table.  All that being said, I will return if I am in the area. Denizens has a full calander of events and live music, and the specials for happy hour are competitive. The menu is simple, and has something for everyone, yet it's not packed with items you could get across the street.
